text:
What up y’all! It’s time 
for a farm kid power anthem!

CRICKET
My name’s Cricket Green

The farm life runs in my blood
Don’t care ‘bout hygiene
Wrestlin’ my pig through the mud

I see city folk
Thinkin’ I’m a joke

But they do not know who I am
And they do not give a yam about me

CRICKET
‘Cause

I’m just a tween-age farm kid, Tilly!
Lookin’ so cool while growing chili!

Don’t give me milk unless 
it’s fresh from the teat!

COW
MOO-OO-OO-OOO

CRICKET
Whoa Tilly,
did you train the cow to sing with perfect pitch?!

TILLY
I’m just bringing out her natural talent!

TILLY
My name’s Tilly Green

I’m livin’ life my own way
I find it serene

Snoozing on a bale of hay
I don’t mean to gloat

I’m friends with a goat
We may not live in a high rise

But every day’s a surprise and here’s why…
‘Cause I’m just a tween-age farm kid, Cricket!
I don’t eat corn unless I pick it!

Who needs a car? I’ll drive 
my sheep on the street!

SHEEP
BAA-AA-AA-AAA

CRICKET
You trained the sheep too?!

TILLY
She’s my star soprano!

CRICKET/TILLY
Oh

yeah! Farm kids!
Harvesting fun here in Big City!

Oh yeah! Farm kids!
Hope you enjoyed our little ditty!

COW
Moooo!
